        {
          "id": "tldr-founders:2023-05-10:o007",
          "order": 3,
          "title": "CREATOR FLYWHEELS",
          "summary": "The article discusses the concept of \"creator flywheels,\" which are self-reinforcing cycles that help creators build and grow their audiences and businesses. By consistently creating content and engaging with their audience, creators can establish trust, grow their following, and increase revenue over time. The author emphasizes the importance of creating habits that contribute to the flywheel's momentum, such as regularly publishing content, launching products, and engaging with the community. By staying committed to these habits, creators can maintain and accelerate the growth of their flywheel, ultimately leading to a successful and sustainable business.",
          "url": "https://nathanbarry.com/creator-flywheels/?utm_source=tldrfounders",
          "reading_time_minutes": 8,
